# Email Service Configuration
# Choose one of the following email services and add the corresponding environment variables

# OPTION 1: Using Ethereal Email (For Testing - No configuration needed)
# Ethereal is Nodemailer's testing service. It works out of the box.
# When emails are sent, you'll get a preview URL in the logs.

# OPTION 2: Using SendGrid
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=your_sendgrid_api_key_here

# OPTION 3: Using Gmail
# GMAIL_USER=your_gmail@gmail.com
# GMAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_password_here
# Note: Use an App Password, not your regular Gmail password
# Generate one at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

# OPTION 4: Using Custom SMTP Server
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.yourdomain.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your_email@yourdomain.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your_password_here

# General Email Settings
CONTACT_EMAIL=test@test.com
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=test@test.com

# Add your environment variables above
